member.summary: Internal collection class for the API. It's defined here so that we can use generics.

member.remarks: jrockwood-2013-01-07: This is where some of the ugly parts of Script# are exposed. We actually define the implementation of this class in the API project in the DoNotUseCollection class. The real name of that class is _Collection, so that when Script# compiles it will use the right implemenation but it will use the type defined in this class. Tricky and hacky, but it's really important to have strongly-typed collections in the API to help maintainability. FIX WHEN MOVING TO SALTARELLE
